               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1300"><!--enter here a marked up description of the date of foundation of this institution--></date>
                  <desc type="foundation">
<!--                  Account of the foundation of the institution   
                        I leave this as an example. note that the description can be fully marked up with reference to other entities.-->
                     Accodring to local tradition, the founder was <persName corresp="PRS99999mamas">ˀabunä Mamas</persName> 
                     (from the time of <persName corresp="PRS12831AdmaS">King ˁAmdä Ṣəyon</persName> I, r. 1314-44).</desc>
                  
                  <ab type="history">
<!--                     Account of the history of the institution 
                     
                     Also this should be removed and substituted with a description of the new institution beeing registered-->
                     Gätär. According to the <ref type="work" target="LIT1231Vita">Vita of saint Bä-ṣälotä Mikaˀel of Däbrä Gol</ref> (ˀAmhara), 
                     he was exiled to <placeName corresp="#LOC9999Gulo">Gulo Mäkäda</placeName> and died at <placeName>Gwədgwəde</placeName>, which seems to have been a name of the area around ˀAgärhǝse. 
                     Local tradition remembers him and confirms that his burial place is in the vicinity. 
                     Tabots (4): Mary, Michael, Mamas, Raphael.</ab>
                  
                  <ab type="description">
<!--                     this block contains the information about the library and can contain references to the manuscripts.-->
